Subject: Re: [T2] Axle differences 71-79

On Sat, 26 Apr 2003, David Newman wrote:

> Can I use any front axle beam of this period on my '79?  A couple I've
> looked at had drum brakes, can I change these over to my disc setup
> (are the spindles the same)?

A '71 shouldn't have drum brakes.  They must be earlier.  '71 and '72 have
different disk brakes with different spindles than your '79, so look for a
'73-up axle.

George
